This is a known breaking change. **.NET 10 adopts Android edge-to-edge mode by default** (required by Android 15+), which means `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` no longer works — Android deprecated it in API 30.

## The Fix

You need to react to **IME (keyboard) window insets** instead. Two approaches:

### Option 1 — Quick fix via `Manifest + Padding` (recommended for chat UIs)

In `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        // Listen for keyboard insets and apply bottom padding
        var content = FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;
        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(content, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }

    private class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

            // Use whichever is larger — keyboard or nav bar
            int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);
            v.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottom);

            return insets;
        }
    }
}
```

### Option 2 — Pure XAML with `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll`

If your input is inside a `ScrollView`, MAUI's built-in auto-scroll should work:

```xml
<ScrollView>
    <Grid RowDefinitions="*, Auto">
        <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ... />
        <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1">
            <Entry Placeholder="Type a message..." HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
            <Button Text="Send" />
        </HorizontalStackLayout>
    </Grid>
</ScrollView>
```

However, for a chat screen with a pinned bottom bar, **Option 1 is more reliable** since it adjusts the entire content area rather than relying on scroll behavior.

### Also remove the old code

Delete any lines like:
```csharp
// No longer works in .NET 10
App.Current.On<Android>()
   .UseWindowSoftInputModeAdjust(WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize);
```

**TL;DR:** Replace the deprecated resize mode with an `OnApplyWindowInsetsListener` that reads `Ime()` insets and sets bottom padding on your root view.
